cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS

This paper is about optimization methods in genetic algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper proposes a new approach to the island model, which involves clustering sub-populations using spectral clustering. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves dynamic control of the number of islands, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on three baseline optimization problems, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
